<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc0013b54-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16276"><num value="16276">§ 16276.</num><heading> Security of nuclear facilities</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall conduct a research and development program on cost-effective technologies for increasing—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc0013b55-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16276/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the safety of nuclear facilities from natural phenomena; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc0013b56-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16276/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the security of nuclear facilities from deliberate attacks.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idc0013b57-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tIX/s956">Pub. L. 109–58, title IX, § 956</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/888">119 Stat. 888</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/115/248/s2/f">Pub. L. 115–248, § 2(f)</ref>, <date date="2018-09-28">Sept. 28, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/3157">132 Stat. 3157</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc0013b58-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc0013b59-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idc0013b5a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2018—<ref href="/us/pl/115/248">Pub. L. 115–248</ref> struck out “, acting through the Director of the Office of Nuclear Energy, Science and Technology,” after “The Secretary” in introductory provisions.</p>
</note>
